T1  - Financial contracts and international lending
AU  - O'Hara, Maureen
JO  - Journal of Banking & Finance
VL  - 14
IS  - 1
SP  - 11
EP  - 31
PY  - 1990
DA  - 1990/03/01/
SN  - 0378-4266
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(90)90032-W
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669090032W
AB  - This paper examines alternative financial contracts for international lending. I demonstrate that conventional loans can be pareto dominated by financial contracts explicitly incorporating characteristics of the borrower's product market. I provide conditions under which commodity-linked debt is desirable, and determine when more complicated revenue-linked loans are optimal. I also demonstrate that the type of lending contract has important real effects on production decisions. One result of this research is to demonstrate why equity-based lending arrangements may have limited applicability.
ER  - 

