AB  - Two types of equilibrium models in bond-markets with taxes exist; the clientele model by Schaefer and the Litzenberger-Rolfo's model. This paper reviews the two models in two frameworks; utility arguments and no-arbitrage arguments. Both show that Schaefer's is more realistic.
