AB  - The Pension Benefit Guarantee Corporation (PBGC) initially insured private pension benefits in exchange for a premium that was not risk sensitive. This paper derives conditions under which a moral hazard problem caused promised pension benefits to increase. The hypotheses are tested using data on individual pension contracts from the pre- and post-PBGC periods.
