DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0378-4266(90)90042-Z
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/037842669090042Z
AB  - This paper develops optimal monetary stabilization rules employing information pertaining to an arbitrary number of financial assets, together with the interest rate. The rules are expressed in terms of an optimal weighted aggregate to be stabilized, with the optimal weights depending upon the variances and covariances of the underlying stochastic disturbances. A generalized Poole-type combination policy is also derived. Properties of the optimal rules are discussed analytically in specific cases. This is supplemented by numerical simulation methods using parameter values based on a disaggregation of the U.S. financial sector into 14 components.
ER  - 

